<p><ent>Kell</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Kell
<hw>Kell</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Caul</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The caul; that which covers or envelops as a caul; a net; a fold; a
film.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll have him cut to the <qex>kell</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. &
Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The cocoon or chrysalis of an insect.</def> <rj><au>
B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Keloid</ent>⟦br⟧
